Every time a heavy rain falls, a number of people in the neighbourhood appear to witness it, kids sticking arms through windows, old ladies, the random guy drinking beer at the balcony. We are here as audience to nature, and are forever bound together in the mystery of her rain.
We will meet tomorrow on a walk outside, we will nod at each other, in the sunny high noon. But the soil will still be a bit wet, we will still remember the storm. There is much comfort in this.
